Andrew and Jon Erwin, known as the '''Erwin Brothers''', are American [[Christian]] film directors, screenwriters and film producers known for such films as ''[[Woodlawn (film)|Woodlawn]]'',<ref>{{cite web|author=McNary, Dave|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/jon-voight-bear-bryant-woodlawn-casting-1201360814/ |title=‘Woodlawn’: Jon Voight Starring as Bear Bryant in Football Movie |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=2014-11-20 |accessdate=2015-08-21}}</ref> ''[[October Baby]]'',<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2012/04/04/movies/october-baby-film-makes-a-dent-at-the-box-office.html?_r=0 The New York Times]</ref> ''[[Moms' Night Out]]''<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/09/movies/moms-night-out-offers-a-christian-themed-comedy.html The New York Times]</ref><ref>[http://www.scriptmag.com/features/writer-profiles/filmmakers-erwin-brothers-schedule-moms-night Scriptmag.com]</ref> and ''[[I Can Only Imagine (film)|I Can Only Imagine]]''.

Their most successful movie to date is ''I Can Only Imagine'', which grossed a worldwide total of $<!-- Please, when you update the gross, change the accessdate as well. Thank you. -->83.5 million against a production budget of $7 million,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.the-numbers.com/movie/I-Can-Only-Imagine#tab=summary |title=''I Can Only Imagine'' (2018) |work=''[[The Numbers (website)|The Numbers]]'' |publisher=Nash Information Services, LLC |accessdate=May 15, 2018}}</ref> with only 1629 theaters for its opening week.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?page=weekly&id=icanonlyimagine.htm |title=''I Can Only Imagine'' (2018). Weekly |work=[[Box Office Mojo]] |publisher=[[Amazon (company)|Amazon]] |accessdate=April 6, 2018}}</ref> The Erwin brothers are the grandsons of Henry Erwin a Medal Of Honor recipient from World War II.

In 2017 the brothers and their filmmaking partner Kevin Downes announced the formation of a new company, Kingdom, that will make a series of original movies that will be distributed through LionsGate. Some will be directed by the Erwins, while other movies will use newcomers and other veteran directors.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bpnews.net/51788/erwins-unveil-next-plans-envision-christian-pixar|title=Erwins unveil next plans, envision 'Christian Pixar'|last=Foust|first=Michael|website=www.bpnews.net|language=en|access-date=2018-11-19}}</ref> Jon Erwin compared it to a "Christian Pixar" or "Christian Marvel." As Baptist Press put it, the company will specialize "in a specific area" -- the faith-based genre -- and be able to "work on multiple films at one time."<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bpnews.net/51788/erwins-unveil-next-plans-envision-christian-pixar|title=Erwins unveil next plans, envision 'Christian Pixar'|last=Foust|first=Michael|website=www.bpnews.net|language=en|access-date=2018-11-19}}</ref>

